"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0728-1462304-olympics-podcast-golden-age-of-swimming-boxing-relief\", \"text\": \"  Mikey Stafford is joined by Irish Olympian Barry Murphy as Mona McSharry wows in the pool and we prepare for Daniel Wiffen to make a splash.  Raf Diallo also reports from the Paris Nord Arena as the Irish boxing team finally got a win on the board in the shape of heavyweight Jack Marley. Raf fills us in on the quarter-final opponent standing between the Sallynoggin native and an Olympic medal.  Then Barry puts some context on McSharry's supreme semi-final performance and looks ahead to Wiffen's 800m heats.  He also explains what swimmers mean by a 'fast pool', while Mikey shares another alcohol-based Olympic story, this time the tale of American swimmer and actress Eleanor Holm.  Listen to the RT\\u00c9 Olympics Podcast on theRT\\u00c9 Radio Player,Apple Podcasts,Spotify, orwherever you get your podcasts  We need your consent to load this rte-player contentWe use rte-player to manage extra content that can set cookies on your device and collect data about your activity. Please review their details and accept them to load the content.Manage Preferences    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"